# QualCoder
QualCoder is a qualitative data analysis application.

QualCoder projects are stored in a Sqlite database. Text files can be typed in manually or loaded from txt, odt, docx, epub and optionally ,and not ideally, pdf files. Codes can be assigned to text, images, audio and video. and grouped into categories in hierarchical fashion. Various types of reports can be produced including visual coding graphs, coder comparisons and coding frequencies.

This project has been tested under Ubuntu 18, Linux Mint 18, Windows 10.
Instructions and other information are avaible here: https://qualcoder.wordpress.com/

## INSTALLATION
You will need to have a python3.x version installed.
You will also need to have pyqt5, lxml, qpdf and vlc

### Install via python/pip

1. It is recommended to create a virtualenvironment, probably should work with `python -m venv venv` which will create a directory named `venv` which is your new virtual environment.
2. activate the new environment: `source venv\bin\activate`
3. Install all the requirements, before cd into the directoy holding the source code of qualcoder: `python -m pip install .`
3b. If you want to install in development mode, which will use the code in your source code directory, use : `python -m pip install -e .`

### Install via apt
All dependent packages should be availabe in ubuntu disco.

### Use 

A deb package is provided however you will most probably need to add unstable
repos as described at https://www.binarytides.com/enable-testing-repo-debian/

